      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "MOTHER GEORGIA (1) is a promising dog in the frame at six of 18 starts including six wins and was in the minors again latest (25.66) over 450m at Ballarat. Solid record at the distance winning five races. Drawn the rails and rates a key runner. PHOENIX TAN (4) had the drop on the lead from the rails draw last start but could only manage third, beaten one length (30.26) at The Meadows in a Grade 5 over 525m. Expected to be in this for a long way. RHYTHMIC ENERGY (3) shapes as hard to beat after winning last start over the 425m at Bendigo in a solid 23.95. Smart winner latest and looks a key chance on that form. BLACK MARVEL (7) should be thereabouts.",
